posts.title: Im driving 4 hours to my home swing state to vote
posts.content:
I don't trust the absentee ballot. My address is in a solid blue county and I don't trust them not to throw away my ballot. I'm thinking of putting a sign on my car the whole way "driving home to vote for trump". My license plate tells where, maybe it will inspire one person to vote knowing I'm driving 4 hours to do it when they see me 2 states away.

I like to listen to the enemy so I listened to MSNBC today, Rachel Vagchow wasn't on but some other bitch was. Just hearsay after hearsay of things Trump said, so desperate. They were begging their viewers to tell their family and friends the things Trump said.

They even had the nerve to talk about how we would have Oligarchs running the country like Musk and Thiel. As if Soros and company isn't our current Oligarch!

They didn't attack his policies once except to paint some drama scenario about an immigrant family getting deported while eating dinner as a family.

What does that tell you when the only thing they can attack is things he said?

Do they realize that Trump is just as much of a not Kamala button that Kamala is a not Trump button? People are excited over her like a gamer gets excited that his Grandma bought him a serial port Joystick she found at a thrift store. That's about the level of effort Kamala has put into courting conservatives.

There are far better candidates than Trump and I don't agree with him on everything but the fact that he's not afraid to say whatever he wants is very important to me. He hasn't said anything you didn't say among friends or even strangers in the early 2000s. And regardless, I don't care how moral or rational he may or may not be. That's what checks and balances are for. He's a vehicle to get rid of the woke shit and immigrants stealing our jobs (Indians especially), giving us bed bugs (funny how they became a thing again after 50 years the moment Obama became president), and driving up our rent, and that's all I care about.

The hardest part of election day is lying to my family convincingly that I voted for Kameltoe so they don't Minneapolis my stuff I have stored there.
